Note: Advanced Reactive Planning System for AI Agents
Note: Implements reactive behaviors, subsumption architecture, behavior trees,
Note: real-time planning, and dynamic response to environmental changes
Note: Competitive with behavior-based robotics and reactive AI systems

Note: Core reactive planning types
Type called "ReactivePlan":
    plan id as String
    plan name as String
    plan type as String  Note: "behavior_tree", "subsumption", "hybrid", "stimulus_response"
    behavior network as BehaviorNetwork
    reactive behaviors as List[ReactiveBehavior]
    plan priorities as List[Float]
    execution context as ExecutionContext
    response time as Integer
    adaptability as Float

Type called "ReactiveBehavior":
    behavior id as String
    behavior name as String
    behavior type as String  Note: "primitive", "composite", "conditional", "emergent"
    trigger conditions as List[TriggerCondition]
    behavior actions as List[BehaviorAction]
    suppression rules as List[SuppressionRule]
    activation level as Float
    priority as Float
    execution frequency as Integer
    resource requirements as Dictionary[String, Float]

Type called "BehaviorNetwork":
    network id as String
    network type as String  Note: "subsumption", "behavior_tree", "finite_state_machine", "neural_network"
    network nodes as List[BehaviorNode]
    network connections as List[BehaviorConnection]
    activation functions as List[ActivationFunction]
    inhibition rules as List[InhibitionRule]
    emergence properties as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BehaviorNode":
    node id as String
    node type as String  Note: "sensor", "actuator", "processing", "coordination", "memory"
    activation state as Float
    threshold as Float
    decay rate as Float
    input connections as List[String]
    output connections as List[String]
    node function as NodeFunction

Type called "BehaviorAction":
    action id as String
    action name as String
    action type as String  Note: "immediate", "deferred", "persistent", "interrupt"
    execution condition as Condition
    action duration as Integer
    action effects as List[Effect]
    resource consumption as Dictionary[String, Float]
    interruption handling as String

Type called "TriggerCondition":
    trigger id as String
    trigger type as String  Note: "environmental", "internal", "temporal", "goal_based"
    condition expression as LogicalExpression
    trigger threshold as Float
    activation delay as Integer
    persistence requirements as Integer
    confidence requirement as Float

Type called "SuppressionRule":
    rule id as String
    suppressor behavior as String
    suppressed behavior as String
    suppression type as String  Note: "complete", "partial", "temporal", "conditional"
    suppression strength as Float
    activation conditions as List[Condition]

Type called "ReactiveAgent":
    agent id as String
    agent type as String  Note: "purely_reactive", "hybrid", "layered"
    sensor interface as SensorInterface
    actuator interface as ActuatorInterface
    behavior repertoire as List[ReactiveBehavior]
    coordination mechanism as CoordinationMechanism
    learning component as Optional[LearningComponent]

Note: Reactive Planning Engine
Process called "create_reactive_planner" that takes config as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let planner be create_reactive_planner_structure
    Set planner with key "planner_id" to generate_reactive_planner_id
    Set planner with key "architecture_type" to config with key "architecture" or "subsumption"
    Set planner with key "response_time_limit" to config with key "max_response_time" or 100
    Set planner with key "behavior_selection" to config with key "selection_mechanism" or "priority_based"
    Set planner with key "learning_enabled" to config with key "learning" or false
    Set planner with key "adaptation_rate" to config with key "adaptation_rate" or 0.1
    Set planner with key "suppression_enabled" to config with key "suppression" or true
    
    Return planner

Process called "create_reactive_plan" that takes planner as Dictionary and problem as ReactivePlanningProblem returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    Set result with key "success" to false
    
    Let architecture_type be planner with key "architecture_type"
    
    If architecture_type is equal to "subsumption":
        Set result to create_subsumption_plan with planner and problem
    
    If architecture_type is equal to "behavior_tree":
        Set result to create_behavior_tree_plan with planner and problem
    
    If architecture_type is equal to "hybrid":
        Set result to create_hybrid_reactive_plan with planner and problem
    
    If architecture_type is equal to "stimulus_response":
        Set result to create_stimulus_response_plan with planner and problem
    
    Return result

Process called "create_subsumption_plan" that takes planner as Dictionary and problem as ReactivePlanningProblem returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    Set result with key "success" to true
    
    Let goals be problem with field goals
    Let environment_model be problem with field environment_model
    Let available_behaviors be problem with field available_behaviors
    
    Note: Create subsumption architecture with layered behaviors
    Let subsumption_layers be create_subsumption_layers with goals and available_behaviors
    
    Note: Organize behaviors by priority (lower layers have higher priority)
    Let prioritized_behaviors be sort_behaviors_by_subsumption_priority with available_behaviors
    
    Note: Create behavior network for subsumption
    Let behavior_network be create_behavior_network_structure
    Set behavior_network with field network_id to generate_network_id
    Set behavior_network with field network_type to "subsumption"
    Set behavior_network with field network_nodes to create_subsumption_nodes with prioritized_behaviors
    Set behavior_network with field network_connections to create_subsumption_connections with prioritized_behaviors
    
    Note: Define suppression rules between layers
    Let suppression_rules be create_subsumption_suppression_rules with prioritized_behaviors
    Set behavior_network with field inhibition_rules to suppression_rules
    
    Note: Create reactive plan
    Let reactive_plan be create_reactive_plan_structure
    Set reactive_plan with field plan_id to generate_reactive_plan_id
    Set reactive_plan with field plan_type to "subsumption"
    Set reactive_plan with field behavior_network to behavior_network
    Set reactive_plan with field reactive_behaviors to prioritized_behaviors
    Set reactive_plan with field response_time to planner with key "response_time_limit"
    
    Let priorities be extract_behavior_priorities with prioritized_behaviors
    Set reactive_plan with field plan_priorities to priorities
    
    Set result with key "plan" to reactive_plan
    Set result with key "architecture_details" to subsumption_layers
    
    Return result

Process called "create_subsumption_layers" that takes goals as List[Goal] and behaviors as List[ReactiveBehavior] returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let layers be empty list
    
    Note: Layer 0: Obstacle avoidance (highest priority)
    Let avoidance_behaviors be filter_behaviors_by_type with behaviors and "obstacle_avoidance"
    If length of avoidance_behaviors is greater than 0:
        Let layer_0 be dictionary with keys "layer_level", "layer_name", "behaviors", "suppresses":
            "layer_level" maps to 0
            "layer_name" maps to "Obstacle Avoidance"
            "behaviors" maps to avoidance_behaviors
            "suppresses" maps to list containing "all_higher_layers"
        Add layer_0 to layers
    
    Note: Layer 1: Wandering/exploration
    Let exploration_behaviors be filter_behaviors_by_type with behaviors and "exploration"
    If length of exploration_behaviors is greater than 0:
        Let layer_1 be dictionary with keys "layer_level", "layer_name", "behaviors", "suppresses":
            "layer_level" maps to 1
            "layer_name" maps to "Exploration"
            "behaviors" maps to exploration_behaviors
            "suppresses" maps to list containing "goal_seeking", "path_following"
        Add layer_1 to layers
    
    Note: Layer 2: Goal seeking
    Let goal_seeking_behaviors be filter_behaviors_by_type with behaviors and "goal_seeking"
    If length of goal_seeking_behaviors is greater than 0:
        Let layer_2 be dictionary with keys "layer_level", "layer_name", "behaviors", "suppresses":
            "layer_level" maps to 2
            "layer_name" maps to "Goal Seeking"
            "behaviors" maps to goal_seeking_behaviors
            "suppresses" maps to empty list
        Add layer_2 to layers
    
    Note: Add custom layers for specific goals
    For each goal in goals:
        Let goal_specific_behaviors be find_behaviors_for_goal with behaviors and goal
        If length of goal_specific_behaviors is greater than 0:
            Let custom_layer be dictionary with keys "layer_level", "layer_name", "behaviors", "goal":
                "layer_level" maps to length of layers
                "layer_name" maps to ("Goal: " concatenated with goal with field goal_name)
                "behaviors" maps to goal_specific_behaviors
                "goal" maps to goal
            Add custom_layer to layers
    
    Return layers

Process called "create_behavior_tree_plan" that takes planner as Dictionary and problem as ReactivePlanningProblem returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    Set result with key "success" to true
    
    Let goals be problem with field goals
    Let available_behaviors be problem with field available_behaviors
    
    Note: Create behavior tree structure
    Let behavior_tree be create_behavior_tree_structure with goals and available_behaviors
    
    Note: Create behavior network for tree execution
    Let behavior_network be create_behavior_network_structure
    Set behavior_network with field network_id to generate_network_id
    Set behavior_network with field network_type to "behavior_tree"
    Set behavior_network with field network_nodes to behavior_tree with key "nodes"
    Set behavior_network with field network_connections to behavior_tree with key "connections"
    
    Note: Create reactive plan
    Let reactive_plan be create_reactive_plan_structure
    Set reactive_plan with field plan_id to generate_reactive_plan_id
    Set reactive_plan with field plan_type to "behavior_tree"
    Set reactive_plan with field behavior_network to behavior_network
    Set reactive_plan with field reactive_behaviors to available_behaviors
    Set reactive_plan with field response_time to planner with key "response_time_limit"
    
    Set result with key "plan" to reactive_plan
    Set result with key "behavior_tree" to behavior_tree
    
    Return result

Process called "create_behavior_tree_structure" that takes goals as List[Goal] and behaviors as List[ReactiveBehavior] returns Dictionary:
    Let tree be empty dictionary
    Set tree with key "tree_id" to generate_behavior_tree_id
    Set tree with key "root_node" to create_root_node with goals
    Set tree with key "nodes" to empty list
    Set tree with key "connections" to empty list
    
    Note: Create root selector node
    Let root_node be create_behavior_tree_node with "root" and "selector" and empty list
    Add root_node to tree with key "nodes"
    
    Note: Create sequences for each goal
    For each goal in goals:
        Let goal_behaviors be find_behaviors_for_goal with behaviors and goal
        Let goal_sequence be create_goal_sequence_node with goal and goal_behaviors
        
        Add goal_sequence to tree with key "nodes"
        
        Note: Connect root to goal sequence
        Let connection be create_tree_connection with root_node with key "node_id" and goal_sequence with key "node_id"
        Add connection to tree with key "connections"
        
        Note: Create behavior nodes for this goal
        For each behavior in goal_behaviors:
            Let behavior_node be create_behavior_execution_node with behavior
            Add behavior_node to tree with key "nodes"
            
            Note: Connect sequence to behavior
            Let behavior_connection be create_tree_connection with goal_sequence with key "node_id" and behavior_node with key "node_id"
            Add behavior_connection to tree with key "connections"
    
    Return tree

Process called "create_goal_sequence_node" that takes goal as Goal and behaviors as List[ReactiveBehavior] returns Dictionary:
    Let sequence_node be create_behavior_tree_node with ("goal_sequence_" concatenated with goal with field goal_id) and "sequence" and behaviors
    Set sequence_node with key "goal_reference" to goal
    Set sequence_node with key "execution_policy" to "sequential"
    Set sequence_node with key "failure_handling" to "restart"
    
    Return sequence_node

Note: Reactive Plan Execution Engine
Process called "execute_reactive_plan" that takes reactive_plan as ReactivePlan and execution_config as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let execution_result be empty dictionary
    Set execution_result with key "execution_id" to generate_execution_id
    Set execution_result with key "reactive_plan" to reactive_plan
    Set execution_result with key "start_time" to current_timestamp
    
    Let plan_type be reactive_plan with field plan_type
    Let behavior_network be reactive_plan with field behavior_network
    Let execution_frequency be execution_config with key "execution_frequency" or 10  Note: Hz
    Let execution_duration be execution_config with key "duration" or 30000  Note: milliseconds
    
    Let execution_trace be empty list
    Let behavior_states be initialize_behavior_states with reactive_plan with field reactive_behaviors
    Let sensor_data be initialize_sensor_interface with execution_config
    
    Let start_time be current_timestamp
    Let cycle_count be 0
    
    Note: Main reactive execution loop
    While current_timestamp minus start_time is less than execution_duration:
        Let cycle_start be current_timestamp
        Set cycle_count to cycle_count plus 1
        
        Note: Sense environment
        Let current_sensor_data be read_sensor_data with sensor_data
        
        Note: Update behavior activations
        Let updated_states be update_behavior_activations with behavior_states and current_sensor_data and reactive_plan
        Set behavior_states to updated_states
        
        Note: Select and execute behaviors
        Let execution_result_cycle be empty dictionary
        
        If plan_type is equal to "subsumption":
            Set execution_result_cycle to execute_subsumption_cycle with behavior_states and current_sensor_data and reactive_plan
        
        If plan_type is equal to "behavior_tree":
            Set execution_result_cycle to execute_behavior_tree_cycle with behavior_states and current_sensor_data and reactive_plan
        
        If plan_type is equal to "hybrid":
            Set execution_result_cycle to execute_hybrid_cycle with behavior_states and current_sensor_data and reactive_plan
        
        Note: Record execution trace
        Let trace_entry be dictionary with keys "cycle", "timestamp", "sensor_data", "behavior_states", "execution_result":
            "cycle" maps to cycle_count
            "timestamp" maps to cycle_start
            "sensor_data" maps to current_sensor_data
            "behavior_states" maps to copy of behavior_states
            "execution_result" maps to execution_result_cycle
        
        Add trace_entry to execution_trace
        
        Note: Handle emergency conditions
        If execution_result_cycle contains key "emergency_stop":
            Set execution_result with key "final_status" to "emergency_stop"
            Set execution_result with key "emergency_reason" to execution_result_cycle with key "emergency_reason"
            Break from loop
        
        Note: Maintain execution frequency
        Let cycle_end be current_timestamp
        Let cycle_duration be cycle_end minus cycle_start
        Let target_cycle_duration be 1000 divided by execution_frequency
        
        If cycle_duration is less than target_cycle_duration:
            Let sleep_time be target_cycle_duration minus cycle_duration
            Wait for sleep_time milliseconds
    
    Note: Finalize execution result
    If execution_result does not contain key "final_status":
        Set execution_result with key "final_status" to "completed"
    
    Set execution_result with key "end_time" to current_timestamp
    Set execution_result with key "execution_trace" to execution_trace
    Set execution_result with key "cycle_count" to cycle_count
    Set execution_result with key "final_behavior_states" to behavior_states
    
    Return execution_result

Process called "execute_subsumption_cycle" that takes behavior_states as Dictionary and sensor_data as Dictionary and reactive_plan as ReactivePlan returns Dictionary:
    Let cycle_result be empty dictionary
    Set cycle_result with key "executed_behaviors" to empty list
    Set cycle_result with key "suppressed_behaviors" to empty list
    Set cycle_result with key "active_layer" to -1
    
    Let behaviors be reactive_plan with field reactive_behaviors
    Let priorities be reactive_plan with field plan_priorities
    
    Note: Sort behaviors by priority (lower priority number = higher precedence)
    Let priority_sorted_behaviors be sort_behaviors_by_priority with behaviors and priorities
    
    Note: Execute highest priority applicable behavior
    For behavior_index from 0 to length of priority_sorted_behaviors minus 1:
        Let behavior be priority_sorted_behaviors with index behavior_index
        Let behavior_id be behavior with field behavior_id
        Let behavior_state be behavior_states with key behavior_id
        
        Note: Check if behavior is triggered and not suppressed
        Let is_triggered be check_behavior_triggers with behavior and sensor_data
        Let is_suppressed be check_behavior_suppression with behavior and behavior_states and reactive_plan
        
        If is_triggered is equal to true and is_suppressed is equal to false:
            Note: Execute this behavior (subsumption - only one behavior executes)
            Let behavior_execution_result be execute_single_behavior with behavior and sensor_data
            
            Add behavior to cycle_result with key "executed_behaviors"
            Set cycle_result with key "active_layer" to behavior_index
            Set cycle_result with key "execution_result" to behavior_execution_result
            
            Note: Suppress all lower priority behaviors
            For suppressed_index from behavior_index plus 1 to length of priority_sorted_behaviors minus 1:
                Let suppressed_behavior be priority_sorted_behaviors with index suppressed_index
                Add suppressed_behavior to cycle_result with key "suppressed_behaviors"
            
            Break from loop
    
    Return cycle_result

Process called "execute_behavior_tree_cycle" that takes behavior_states as Dictionary and sensor_data as Dictionary and reactive_plan as ReactivePlan returns Dictionary:
    Let cycle_result be empty dictionary
    Set cycle_result with key "executed_behaviors" to empty list
    Set cycle_result with key "tree_execution_status" to "running"
    
    Let behavior_network be reactive_plan with field behavior_network
    Let tree_nodes be behavior_network with field network_nodes
    
    Note: Find root node and execute tree from top
    Let root_node be find_root_node with tree_nodes
    
    If root_node is not equal to null:
        Let tree_execution_result be execute_behavior_tree_node with root_node and tree_nodes and sensor_data and behavior_states
        
        Set cycle_result with key "tree_execution_status" to tree_execution_result with key "status"
        Set cycle_result with key "executed_behaviors" to tree_execution_result with key "executed_behaviors"
        Set cycle_result with key "tree_state" to tree_execution_result with key "tree_state"
    
    Return cycle_result

Process called "execute_behavior_tree_node" that takes node as Dictionary and all_nodes as List[Dictionary] and sensor_data as Dictionary and behavior_states as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let execution_result be empty dictionary
    Set execution_result with key "status" to "running"
    Set execution_result with key "executed_behaviors" to empty list
    Set execution_result with key "tree_state" to empty dictionary
    
    Let node_type be node with key "node_type"
    
    If node_type is equal to "selector":
        Set execution_result to execute_selector_node with node and all_nodes and sensor_data and behavior_states
    
    If node_type is equal to "sequence":
        Set execution_result to execute_sequence_node with node and all_nodes and sensor_data and behavior_states
    
    If node_type is equal to "parallel":
        Set execution_result to execute_parallel_node with node and all_nodes and sensor_data and behavior_states
    
    If node_type is equal to "behavior_execution":
        Set execution_result to execute_behavior_execution_node with node and sensor_data and behavior_states
    
    If node_type is equal to "condition":
        Set execution_result to execute_condition_node with node and sensor_data
    
    Return execution_result

Process called "execute_selector_node" that takes node as Dictionary and all_nodes as List[Dictionary] and sensor_data as Dictionary and behavior_states as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    Set result with key "status" to "failure"
    Set result with key "executed_behaviors" to empty list
    
    Let child_nodes be find_child_nodes with node and all_nodes
    
    Note: Try each child until one succeeds
    For each child in child_nodes:
        Let child_result be execute_behavior_tree_node with child and all_nodes and sensor_data and behavior_states
        
        Let child_behaviors be child_result with key "executed_behaviors"
        Set result with key "executed_behaviors" to concatenate with result with key "executed_behaviors" and child_behaviors
        
        If child_result with key "status" is equal to "success":
            Set result with key "status" to "success"
            Break from loop
        
        If child_result with key "status" is equal to "running":
            Set result with key "status" to "running"
            Break from loop
    
    Return result

Process called "execute_sequence_node" that takes node as Dictionary and all_nodes as List[Dictionary] and sensor_data as Dictionary and behavior_states as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    Set result with key "status" to "success"
    Set result with key "executed_behaviors" to empty list
    
    Let child_nodes be find_child_nodes with node and all_nodes
    
    Note: Execute all children in sequence - all must succeed
    For each child in child_nodes:
        Let child_result be execute_behavior_tree_node with child and all_nodes and sensor_data and behavior_states
        
        Let child_behaviors be child_result with key "executed_behaviors"
        Set result with key "executed_behaviors" to concatenate with result with key "executed_behaviors" and child_behaviors
        
        If child_result with key "status" is equal to "failure":
            Set result with key "status" to "failure"
            Break from loop
        
        If child_result with key "status" is equal to "running":
            Set result with key "status" to "running"
            Break from loop
    
    Return result

Note: Behavior Learning and Adaptation
Process called "adapt_reactive_behaviors" that takes reactive_plan as ReactivePlan and execution_history as List[Dictionary] and adaptation_config as Dictionary returns ReactivePlan:
    Let adapted_plan be copy of reactive_plan
    Let behaviors be adapted_plan with field reactive_behaviors
    Let adaptation_rate be adaptation_config with key "learning_rate" or 0.1
    
    Note: Analyze behavior performance from execution history
    Let behavior_performance be analyze_behavior_performance with execution_history
    
    Note: Adapt behavior priorities based on success rates
    For each behavior in behaviors:
        Let behavior_id be behavior with field behavior_id
        
        If behavior_performance contains key behavior_id:
            Let performance_data be behavior_performance with key behavior_id
            Let success_rate be performance_data with key "success_rate"
            Let current_priority be behavior with field priority
            
            Note: Increase priority for successful behaviors
            If success_rate is greater than 0.8:
                Let new_priority be current_priority minus (adaptation_rate multiplied by (success_rate minus 0.8))
                Set behavior with field priority to maximum of 0.1 and new_priority
            
            Note: Decrease priority for unsuccessful behaviors
            If success_rate is less than 0.5:
                Let new_priority be current_priority plus (adaptation_rate multiplied by (0.5 minus success_rate))
                Set behavior with field priority to minimum of 10.0 and new_priority
    
    Note: Adapt trigger conditions based on environmental patterns
    Let trigger_adaptations be analyze_trigger_effectiveness with execution_history
    
    For each behavior in behaviors:
        Let behavior_id be behavior with field behavior_id
        
        If trigger_adaptations contains key behavior_id:
            Let trigger_data be trigger_adaptations with key behavior_id
            Let trigger_conditions be behavior with field trigger_conditions
            
            Note: Adjust trigger thresholds based on false positive/negative rates
            For each trigger_condition in trigger_conditions:
                Let condition_id be trigger_condition with field trigger_id
                
                If trigger_data contains key condition_id:
                    Let adaptation_info be trigger_data with key condition_id
                    Let current_threshold be trigger_condition with field trigger_threshold
                    Let threshold_adjustment be adaptation_info with key "recommended_adjustment"
                    
                    Let new_threshold be current_threshold plus (adaptation_rate multiplied by threshold_adjustment)
                    Set trigger_condition with field trigger_threshold to new_threshold
    
    Note: Update plan priorities
    Let updated_priorities be extract_updated_priorities with behaviors
    Set adapted_plan with field plan_priorities to updated_priorities
    
    Return adapted_plan

Process called "analyze_behavior_performance" that takes execution_history as List[Dictionary] returns Dictionary:
    Let performance_analysis be empty dictionary
    
    Note: Aggregate performance data for each behavior
    For each execution_trace in execution_history:
        Let trace_entries be execution_trace with key "execution_trace"
        
        For each trace_entry in trace_entries:
            Let execution_result be trace_entry with key "execution_result"
            
            If execution_result contains key "executed_behaviors":
                Let executed_behaviors be execution_result with key "executed_behaviors"
                
                For each behavior in executed_behaviors:
                    Let behavior_id be behavior with field behavior_id
                    
                    If performance_analysis contains key behavior_id:
                        Let existing_data be performance_analysis with key behavior_id
                        Set existing_data with key "execution_count" to existing_data with key "execution_count" plus 1
                        
                        Note: Assume success if no error reported
                        If execution_result does not contain key "error":
                            Set existing_data with key "success_count" to existing_data with key "success_count" plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Let new_data be dictionary with keys "execution_count", "success_count":
                            "execution_count" maps to 1
                            "success_count" maps to 1
                        Set performance_analysis with key behavior_id to new_data
    
    Note: Calculate success rates
    For each behavior_id in keys of performance_analysis:
        Let behavior_data be performance_analysis with key behavior_id
        Let execution_count be behavior_data with key "execution_count"
        Let success_count be behavior_data with key "success_count"
        
        Let success_rate be success_count as Float divided by execution_count as Float
        Set behavior_data with key "success_rate" to success_rate
    
    Return performance_analysis

Note: Main reactive planning coordination
Process called "create_reactive_planning_system" that takes configuration as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let system be empty dictionary
    Set system with key "architecture_types" to configuration with key "architectures" or list containing "subsumption", "behavior_tree", "hybrid"
    Set system with key "behavior_selection" to configuration with key "selection" or list containing "priority_based", "utility_based"
    Set system with key "learning_enabled" to configuration with key "learning" or true
    Set system with key "real_time_constraints" to configuration with key "real_time" or true
    Set system with key "adaptation_mechanisms" to configuration with key "adaptation" or list containing "priority_adaptation", "threshold_adaptation"
    
    Return system

Process called "execute_reactive_planning_analysis" that takes system as Dictionary and query as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let query_type be query with key "type"
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    If query_type is equal to "create_reactive_plan":
        Let problem be query with key "problem"
        Let planner_config be query with key "planner_config"
        
        Let planner be create_reactive_planner with planner_config
        Let planning_result be create_reactive_plan with planner and problem
        Set result with key "reactive_planning_result" to planning_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "execute_reactive_plan":
        Let reactive_plan be query with key "reactive_plan"
        Let execution_config be query with key "execution_config"
        
        Let execution_result be execute_reactive_plan with reactive_plan and execution_config
        Set result with key "execution_result" to execution_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "adapt_behaviors":
        Let reactive_plan be query with key "reactive_plan"
        Let execution_history be query with key "execution_history"
        Let adaptation_config be query with key "adaptation_config"
        
        Let adapted_plan be adapt_reactive_behaviors with reactive_plan and execution_history and adaptation_config
        Set result with key "adapted_plan" to adapted_plan
    
    If query_type is equal to "analyze_performance":
        Let execution_history be query with key "execution_history"
        
        Let performance_analysis be analyze_behavior_performance with execution_history
        Set result with key "performance_analysis" to performance_analysis
    
    If query_type is equal to "create_behavior_tree":
        Let goals be query with key "goals"
        Let behaviors be query with key "behaviors"
        
        Let behavior_tree be create_behavior_tree_structure with goals and behaviors
        Set result with key "behavior_tree" to behavior_tree
    
    Note: Add metadata
    Set result with key "reactive_planning_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    Set result with key "system_config" to extract_system_summary with system
    
    Return result